OL,3,CCouncil fined after man falls while
OL,4,Cinstalling town's Christmas tree
OL,6,FA council has been fined #200,000
OL,7,Fafter an employee was injured while
OL,8,Fputting up the town's Christmas tree.
OL,10,FJames Lyth, who worked for Bury
OL,11,FCouncil, was using a scissor lift to
OL,12,Fstraighten the 20-foot tall Christmas
OL,13,Ftree when it toppled over with him
OL,14,Fstill in the basket.
OL,16,FThe tree was being installed by an
OL,17,Fexternal company at Bury Market on 21
OL,18,FNovember 2022 when the accident
OL,19,Fhappened.
